name: phosphoric acid factory construction, fertiliser grade | phosphoric acid factory, fertiliser grade | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/1935/documentation

Large uncertainties for equipment used due to weak data from a small pilot plant. Process refers to an phosphoric acid plant using with 65'000 t phosphoric acid (as 100% H3PO4) production per year. Assumed life time 50 years.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]

Estimation of infrastructure from wet-phosphoric acid production plant including building materials and material for processing equipment. Transport of materials to construction site. Dismaterling of plant and disposal. Land useand occupation for plant.
category: F:Construction/41:Construction of buildings/410:Construction of buildings/4100:Construction of buildings
tags: Sector: Infrastructure & Machinery; Chemicals; Agriculture & Animal Husbandry

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Estimated data refers on a plant built in Jordania. Land use considered from a large plant in Florida. Land use asessed and extrapoleated with data of a mayor site in Florida.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Estimated. No specific technology modelled. Tranport requirement of steel cylinder included.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Infrastructure data from one small plant applied for the whole production. Therefore very high uncertainity. This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography US. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Estimation of the infrastructure will have low representativity because they were asessed with data from a small scale plant.
